Known only from three localities in northern Botswana and north-central Namibia (Fig. 
56
). A rarely collected species known only from three specimens and two collecting events in 1930 and 1948 and one observation in 2019 (Table 
1
). The species is not known to occur in any currently recognized biodiversity hotspot. Adult flies are active in June-July in mid winter (Table 
2
), which corresponds to the dry season and lower temperatures (data for Kasane, Botswana, see https://worldweather.wmo.int/en/city.html?cityId=1545 and Oshikango, Namibia, see https://www.worldweatheronline.com/oshikango-weather-averages/ohangwena/na.aspx). Nothing is known of the biology.
